lead_paragraph: China should release at least 76 people, detained on the mainland for supporting Hong Kong's pro-democracy protests, before the start of next week's Asia-Pacific leaders summit in Beijing, rights group Amnesty International said on Friday.

headline.main: Amnesty Calls for Release of Pro-HK Activists Before APEC Summit
headline.print_headline: Amnesty Calls for Release of Pro-HK Activists Before APEC Summit
